HEADWORD: Combativeness
<hw>Com"bat*ive*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality of
being combative; propensity to contend or to quarrel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Phren.)</fld> <def>A cranial development supposed
to indicate a combative disposition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Combattant</ent>⟦br⟧
